    "coverage_notes": "Full USN Rev 7 Table 9-7 air ladder, depths 25-190 fsw (every tabulated depth: 25,30,35,40,45,50,55,60,70,80,90,100,110,120,130,140,150,160,170,180,190). Each row carries the real No-Stop Limit (min) and the complete repetitive-group column (A-O plus Z where tabulated); each group's max_time_min is the manual's cumulative bottom-time value, and the last (highest) group's max_time equals the NDL. Transcribed by rendering page 9-63 of the Rev 7 tables PDF at 300-450 DPI and cross-mapping every cell to its column by coordinate (header letter x-centers), then re-verifying against the rendered image. The three shallowest manual rows (10/15/20 fsw) are DELIBERATELY OMITTED because their No-Stop Limit is 'Unlimited', which cannot be represented as a finite float in this schema (engine get_ndl does float(ndl_min)); shallow nitrox EAD lookups round up to 25 fsw instead. Confidence: HIGH (single authoritative Rev 7 source, coordinate-verified, internal monotonicity + last-group==NDL checks pass). Not yet cross-checked against a second independent Rev 7 source (UHMS TT2A PDF turned out to be a treatment table, not the air tables).",
